                            <comment id="15268165" author="abalmin" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 06:08:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vsparmar&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vsparmar&quot;&gt;vsparmar&lt;/a&gt; I don&apos;t  know for sure - I don&apos;t work on Spark - I just use it. It is clearly a Spark SQL issue, mostly likely, due to some incorrect rewrites in the catalyst module. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15270423" author="vsparmar" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 09:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As I was trying to look into the issue but got stuck at &quot;catalyst module&quot; ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried to get more information about it and came to conclusion that, you are trying to refer to Catalyst optimizer, which leverages advanced programming language features (e.g. Scala&#8217;s pattern matching and quasiquotes) in a novel way to build an extensible query optimizer. And trying to point towards &apos;org.apache.spark.sql.catalyst.util&quot; !!&lt;/p&gt;

